              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1" syriaca-tags="scribal-colophon ownership-inscription">
                    <locus from="137b" to="138"/>
                    <p>Beneath <ref target="#a1">the final rubric</ref>, are the words <quote xml:lang="syr">ܒܪܝܟ ܐܠܗܐ ܠܥܠܡ̣. ܘܡܫܒܚ ܫܡܗ̣ ܠܕܪܕܪܝܢ</quote>, followed by the doxology.</p>                    
                    <p>A long note, filling up the whole of the second column of <locus from="137b">this page</locus>, has been most carefully effaced. At the beginning of its second paragraph, we can just decipher the words <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܕܬܠܡ̈ܝܕܘܗܝ ܕܚܣܝܐ ܐܒܘܢ ܡܪܝ ܓܐܘܪܓܝ : ܐܠܐ</quote>, <quote>This book belongs to the disciples of the bishop, our father <persName ref="">Mar George</persName>; but—</quote>.</p>
                    <p>On the remaining fragment of fol. <locus from="138">138</locus>, we read part of the original colophon: <quote xml:lang="syr">ܠܐ ܡܪܝ ܢܬܛܠܡ ܐܓܪܐ ܕܚܡܫ ܬܐ̈ܡܬܐ ܕܥܠܡܠ ܙܪܥ̣ ܙܪܥܟ ܡܡܕܟ ܒܣܡ̈ܡܢܐ ܒܚܩܠܐ ܕܚ̈ܝܘܬܐ ܒܐܒܪ̈ܐ ܕܦܪ̈ܚܬܐ ܒܚܝܠܐ ܕܐܠܗܐ܀</quote></p>
                      <p><quote>Lord, let not be unjustly withheld the reward of the five pairs</quote> (the fingers), <quote>which have laboured (and) sown thy seed, mixed with pigments, on the field of animals</quote> (the vellum), <quote>with the quills of birds, through the strength of God.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2" syriaca-tags="ownership-inscription">
                    <locus from="137b"/>
                    <p>The perpetrator of this outrage of effacement was <persName ref="">Isaac bar Abraham bar Dinārā of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/193">Tagrit</placeName></persName>, who has recorded his purchase of the volume in these words:</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">܀ ܒܪܗ ܕܐܒܐ ܒܪܗ ܕܒܬܘܠܬܐ ܝܫܘܥ ܡܫܝܚܐ. ܐܠܗܐ ܫܪܝܫܐ ܘܡܒܪܟܐ ܕܠܥܠܡܝܢ. ܚܘܢ ܒܪ̈ܚܡܝܟ ܣ̈ܓܝܐܐ ܒܥܠܡܐ ܗܢܐ ܘܒܥܠܡܐ ܕܥܬܝܕ ܠܐܝܣܚܩ ܒܪ ܐܒܪܗܡ ܒܪ ܕܝܢܪܐ ܬܓܪܝܬܢܝܐ ܕܩܢܝܗܝ ܠܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܐܝܟ ܕܠܝܘܬܪܢܐ ܕܩܢܘܡܗ. ܏ܘܫ.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
